cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY

This paper discusses a specific sampling technique, Gibbs sampling, which is commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analyzing the mixing times of the sampling technique, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves studying the conductance of the state space, which falls under the category of information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the hardware implementation of the sampling technique, which falls under the category of systems and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
